adjectives.description: implantable (comparative more implantable, superlative most implantable)

entries.meaning: Capable of being, or designed to be, implanted (within the body etc.)
A device that can be implanted surgically.
examples: I've had the opportunity to work on mouthwashes and astringents, catheter antimicrobial treatments, and antimicrobial treatments of other implantables and insertables.
